Key Aspects of AWS:
Core Services: The most popular services include compute (Amazon EC2), storage (Amazon S3), databases (Amazon RDS), and serverless computing (AWS Lambda).
Global Infrastructure: AWS operates in multiple geographic regions and Availability Zones (AZs) worldwide, allowing for low-latency, high-availability deployments.
Key Benefits: Provides scalability, flexibility, and cost-efficiency (pay only for what you use), enabling users to offload IT infrastructure management.
Security & Compliance: Operates under a shared responsibility model, where AWS manages infrastructure security while customers secure their applications and data.
